20#ifndef _ELF_RL78_H
21#define _ELF_RL78_H
22
23#include "elf/reloc-macros.h"
24
25/* Note that there are a few internal relocation types used by the
26 linker to do link-time relaxation. If you update this file, please
27 check elf32-rl78.c to see if any of the internal relocations need to
28 be, er, relocated. */
29
30/* Preliminary relocations. */
31START_RELOC_NUMBERS (elf_rl78_reloc_type)
32
33 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_NONE, 0x00)
34 /* These are for data, and are bi-endian. */
35 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR32, 0x01) /* Was: R_RL78_32. */
36 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR24S, 0x02) /* Was: R_RL78_24. */
37 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16, 0x03)
38 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16U, 0x04) /* Was: R_RL78_16_UNS. */
39 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16S, 0x05) /* Was: R_RL78_16. */
40 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8, 0x06)
41 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8U, 0x07) /* Was: R_RL78_8_UNS. */
42 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8S, 0x08) /* Was: R_RL78_8. */
43
44 /* Signed pc-relative values. */
45 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR24S_PCREL, 0x09) /* Was: R_RL78_24_PCREL. */
46 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16S_PCREL, 0x0a) /* Was: R_RL78_16_PCREL. */
47 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8S_PCREL, 0x0b) /* Was: R_RL78_8_PCREL. */
48
49 /* These are for fields in the instructions. */
50 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16UL, 0x0c)
51 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16UW, 0x0d)
52 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8UL, 0x0e)
53 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR8UW, 0x0f)
54 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR32_REV, 0x10)
55 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR16_REV, 0x11)
56 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_DIR3U_PCREL, 0x12)
57
58 /* These are extensions added by Red Hat. */
59 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_RH_RELAX, 0x2d) /* Marks opcodes suitable for linker relaxation. */
60 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_RH_SFR, 0x2e) /* SFR addresses - internal use only. */
61 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_RH_SADDR, 0x2f) /* SADDR addresses - internal use only.. */
62
63 /* These are for complex relocs. */
64 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS32, 0x41)
65 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS24S, 0x42)
66 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16, 0x43)
67 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16U, 0x44)
68 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16S, 0x45)
69 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8, 0x46)
70 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8U, 0x47)
71 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8S, 0x48)
72 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS24S_PCREL, 0x49)
73 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16S_PCREL, 0x4a)
74 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8S_PCREL, 0x4b)
75 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16UL, 0x4c)
76 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16UW, 0x4d)
77 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8UL, 0x4e)
78 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS8UW, 0x4f)
79 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS32_REV, 0x50)
80 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_ABS16_REV, 0x51)
81
82 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_SYM, 0x80)
83 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPneg, 0x81)
84 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPadd, 0x82)
85 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPsub, 0x83)
86 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPmul, 0x84)
87 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPdiv, 0x85)
88 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPshla, 0x86)
89 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPshra, 0x87)
90 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPsctsize, 0x88)
91 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPscttop, 0x8d)
92 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPand, 0x90)
93 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPor, 0x91)
94 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPxor, 0x92)
95 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPnot, 0x93)
96 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPmod, 0x94)
97 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPromtop, 0x95)
98 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RL78_OPramtop, 0x96)
99
100END_RELOC_NUMBERS (R_RL78_max)
101
102#define EF_RL78_CPU_RL78 0x00000079 /* FIXME: correct value? */
103#define EF_RL78_CPU_MASK 0x0000007F /* specific cpu bits. */
104#define EF_RL78_ALL_FLAGS (EF_RL78_CPU_MASK)
105
106/* Values for the e_flags field in the ELF header. */
107#define E_FLAG_RL78_64BIT_DOUBLES (1 << 0)
108#define E_FLAG_RL78_DSP (1 << 1) /* Defined in the RL78 CPU Object file specification, but not explained. */
109#define E_FLAG_RL78_CPU_MASK 0x0c
110#define E_FLAG_RL78_ANY_CPU 0x00 /* CPU not specified. Assume no CPU specific code usage. */
111#define E_FLAG_RL78_G10 0x04 /* CPU is missing register banks 1-3, so uses different ABI. */
112#define E_FLAG_RL78_G13 0x08 /* CPU uses a peripheral for multiply/divide. */
113#define E_FLAG_RL78_G14 0x0c /* CPU has multiply/divide instructions. */
114
115/* These define the addend field of R_RL78_RH_RELAX relocations. */
116#define RL78_RELAXA_MASK 0x000000f0 /* Mask for relax types */
117#define RL78_RELAXA_BRA 0x00000010 /* Any type of branch (must be decoded). */
118#define RL78_RELAXA_ADDR16 0x00000020 /* addr16->sfr/saddr opportunity */
119#define RL78_RELAXA_RNUM 0x0000000f /* Number of associated relocations. */
120/* These mark the place where alignment is requested, and the place where the filler bytes end. */
121#define RL78_RELAXA_ALIGN 0x10000000 /* Start alignment; the remaining bits are the alignment value. */
122#define RL78_RELAXA_ELIGN 0x20000000 /* End alignment; the remaining bits are the alignment value. */
123#define RL78_RELAXA_ANUM 0x00ffffff /* Alignment amount, in bytes (i.e. .balign). */
124
125#endif /* _ELF_RL78_H */
